[% META
        title = "OPNsense VM on R710 with Proxmox, Kubernetes & Docker Failover Setup"
   description = "Complete guide for deploying OPNsense VM on Dell R710 with Proxmox, Docker-enabled Kubernetes cluster, and automatic failover to physical Dell 210"
   roles = "admin,developer"
   TemplateType = "Documentation"
   category = "infrastructure"
   page_version = "1.0"
   last_updated = "Thu Oct 17 09:09:29 AM PST 2024"
   site_specific = "false"
%]
[% PageVersion = 'Documentation/developer/opnsense_vm_proxmox_k8s_setup.tt,v 1.0 09:09:29 2024/10/17 shanta Exp shanta - OPNsense VM Infrastructure Setup with Failover' %]
[% IF c.session.debug_mode == 1 %]
    [% PageVersion %]
[% END %]

<div class="container">
    <h1 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">OPNsense VM on Dell R710 with Proxmox, Kubernetes & Docker Failover Setup</h1>
    
    <div class="last-updated" style="color: var(--text-muted-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">
        Last Updated: October 17, 2024 | 
        Version: 1.0 | 
        Author: Infrastructure Team | 
        Status: Active
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Overview</h2>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">This guide provides a comprehensive, step-by-step deployment of an OPNsense virtual machine on a Dell PowerEdge R710 server using Proxmox VE as the hypervisor. The setup includes a Kubernetes cluster with Docker runtime in a separate VM for containerized services, and implements automatic failover to a physical Dell 210 using CARP (Common Address Redundancy Protocol) for high availability.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-50">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Prerequisites</h2>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>Dell R710:</strong> BIOS 2.9.x, iDRAC enabled, 16GB+ RAM, 2+ NICs</li>
                <li><strong>Storage:</strong> 100GB+ (SSD recommended for boot)</li>
                <li><strong>Physical Dell 210:</strong> OPNsense installed and backed up (XML config)</li>
                <li><strong>Network:</strong> Separate WAN/LAN switch ports, shared CARP subnet</li>
                <li><strong>Downloads:</strong> Proxmox 8.2, OPNsense 24.7, Ubuntu 24.04 ISOs</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="col-50">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Key Features</h2>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>High Availability:</strong> CARP-based automatic failover with sub-second switchover</li>
                <li><strong>Containerization:</strong> Docker-enabled Kubernetes cluster for auxiliary services</li>
                <li><strong>Monitoring:</strong> K8s-based readiness probes for failover automation</li>
                <li><strong>Scalability:</strong> Foundation for MetalLB load balancing and worker node expansion</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <div class="warning" style="background-color: var(--light-color); border-left: 4px solid var(--warning-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <h3 style="color: var(--warning-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Critical Warnings</h3>
                <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                    <li><strong>Lab Testing Required:</strong> Test in isolated environment—misconfiguring CARP can lock you out</li>
                    <li><strong>RAID Controller:</strong> Flash R710's PERC to IT mode if using ZFS (via sas2flash tool)</li>
                    <li><strong>Network Isolation:</strong> No internet in K8s pods during initial setup; use host networking for OPNsense</li>
                    <li><strong>Time Requirement:</strong> Total setup time: 4-6 hours</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Section 1: Proxmox VE Installation on R710</h2>
            
            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Step 1: Prepare Boot Media</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">Download Proxmox VE 8.2 ISO and create bootable USB media.</p>
            
            <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code>
# On Linux - create bootable USB
dd if=proxmox-ve_8.2-1.iso of=/dev/sdX bs=1M status=progress

# On Windows - use Rufus or similar tool
                </code></pre>
            </div>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Step 2: Install Proxmox</h3>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>Boot from USB, select "Install Proxmox VE"</li>
                <li>Target disk: Use onboard PERC 6/i or H700 with RAID1 for boot (Ctrl+R during POST)</li>
                <li>Set hostname: <code>pve-r710</code></li>
                <li>Management IP: <code>192.168.1.10/24</code>, gateway <code>192.168.1.1</code></li>
                <li>Complete install, reboot, remove USB</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Step 3: Post-Install Configuration</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">Access web UI at <code>https://192.168.1.10:8006</code> and perform initial setup:</p>
            
            <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code>
# Update system
apt update && apt full-upgrade -y && reboot

# Configure network bridges
# vmbr0: eno1 (LAN) - bridge mode
# vmbr1: eno2 (WAN) - bridge mode

# Enable IOMMU for PCI passthrough
echo 'GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX_DEFAULT="quiet intel_iommu=on"' >> /etc/default/grub
update-grub && reboot
                </code></pre>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Section 2: OPNsense VM Creation</h2>
            
            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">VM Specifications</h3>
            <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0;">
                <tr>
                    <th style="background-color: var(--table-header-bg); color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Parameter</th>
                    <th style="background-color: var(--table-header-bg); color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Value</th>
                    <th style="background-color: var(--table-header-bg); color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Purpose</th>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">VM ID</td>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">100</td>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">OPNsense firewall VM</td>
                </tr>
                <tr style="background-color: var(--secondary-color);">
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Memory</td>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">2048 MiB</td>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Sufficient for routing/firewall</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">CPU</td>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">2-4 cores (host type)</td>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Network processing power</td>
                </tr>
                <tr style="background-color: var(--secondary-color);">
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Storage</td>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">32GB qcow2</td>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">OS and configuration</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Network</td>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">vmbr1 (WAN), vmbr0 (LAN)</td>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Dual-NIC firewall setup</td>
                </tr>
            </table>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">OPNsense Installation & Configuration</h3>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>Boot OPNsense ISO, install with UFS filesystem</li>
                <li>Assign interfaces: em0 (WAN), em1 (LAN)</li>
                <li>Set WAN: DHCP or static per ISP requirements</li>
                <li>Set LAN: Static 192.168.1.1/24, enable DHCP pool 192.168.1.100-200</li>
                <li>Access web UI: https://192.168.1.1 (root/opnsense)</li>
            </ul>

            <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); border-left: 4px solid var(--info-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <h4 style="color: var(--info-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">PCI Passthrough (Optional - for Low Latency)</h4>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">For maximum network performance, consider PCI passthrough of dedicated network cards:</p>
                <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                    <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code>
# Identify PCIe cards
lspci | grep -i ethernet

# Configure VFIO passthrough
echo "options vfio-pci ids=8086:1521" >> /etc/modprobe.d/vfio.conf
echo "vfio" >> /etc/modules
echo "vfio_iommu_type1" >> /etc/modules
echo "vfio_pci" >> /etc/modules
update-initramfs -u -k all && reboot
                    </code></pre>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Section 3: Docker-Enabled Kubernetes VM</h2>
            
            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Kubernetes VM Creation</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">Create VM ID 101 with Ubuntu 24.04, 8GB RAM, 4 CPU cores, 64GB storage.</p>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Docker Installation</h3>
            <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code>
# Install Docker
apt update && apt install -y docker.io containerd.io

# Configure Docker daemon
cat > /etc/docker/daemon.json << EOF
{
  "exec-opts": ["native.cgroupdriver=systemd"]
}
EOF

systemctl restart docker && systemctl enable docker
                </code></pre>
            </div>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Kubernetes Cluster Setup</h3>
            <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code>
# Disable swap
swapoff -a
sed -i '/swap/d' /etc/fstab

# Add Kubernetes repository
curl -fsSL https://pkgs.k8s.io/core:/stable:/v1.30/deb/Release.key | gpg --dearmor -o /etc/apt/keyrings/kubernetes-apt-keyring.gpg
echo 'deb [signed-by=/etc/apt/keyrings/kubernetes-apt-keyring.gpg] https://pkgs.k8s.io/core:/stable:/v1.30/deb/ /' | tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/kubernetes.list

# Install Kubernetes components
apt update && apt install -y kubelet kubeadm kubectl
systemctl enable kubelet

# Initialize cluster
kubeadm init --pod-network-cidr=10.244.0.0/16

# Configure kubectl
mkdir -p $HOME/.kube
cp -i /etc/kubernetes/admin.conf $HOME/.kube/config
chown $(id -u):$(id -g) $HOME/.kube/config

# Install Flannel CNI
kubectl apply -f https://raw.githubusercontent.com/flannel-io/flannel/master/Documentation/kube-flannel.yml

# Allow workloads on master node
kubectl taint nodes --all node-role.kubernetes.io/control-plane-
                </code></pre>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Section 4: CARP Failover Configuration</h2>
            
            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Virtual OPNsense (Backup) CARP Setup</h3>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>Firewall → Virtual IPs → Add:</strong></li>
                <li>Type: CARP</li>
                <li>Interface: LAN</li>
                <li>IP Address: 192.168.1.1/24 (VIP)</li>
                <li>VHID Group: 1</li>
                <li>Skew: 100 (higher = lower priority - BACKUP)</li>
                <li>Password: shared_secret</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Physical Dell 210 (Primary) CARP Setup</h3>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>Mirror Virtual Configuration:</strong></li>
                <li>Same CARP VIP settings</li>
                <li>Skew: 0 (highest priority - MASTER)</li>
                <li><strong>High Availability Settings:</strong></li>
                <li>Primary IP: Dell 210 LAN IP</li>
                <li>Backup IP: Virtual OPNsense LAN IP</li>
                <li>Enable Config Sync and State Sync</li>
            </ul>

            <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); border-left: 4px solid var(--success-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <h4 style="color: var(--success-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">CARP Status Verification</h4>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">After configuration, verify CARP status:</p>
                <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                    <li>Dell 210: Should show "MASTER" state</li>
                    <li>Virtual OPNsense: Should show "BACKUP" state</li>
                    <li>Test failover by shutting down Dell 210 - Virtual should promote to MASTER</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Section 5: Kubernetes Failover Automation</h2>
            
            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">OPNsense Readiness Probe</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">Deploy monitoring pod to watch OPNsense VM health and trigger failover:</p>
            
            <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code>
# Create opnsense-monitor.yaml
cat > opnsense-monitor.yaml << EOF
apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: opnsense-failover-monitor
spec:
  schedule: "*/2 * * * *"  # Every 2 minutes
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: monitor
            image: curlimages/curl:latest
            command: ["/bin/sh", "-c"]
            args:
            - |
              # Check OPNsense VM health
              if ! curl -f -k --max-time 10 https://192.168.1.1; then
                echo "OPNsense VM failed health check"
                # Trigger Dell 210 promotion via CARP API
                curl -X POST -k -u "API_KEY:API_SECRET" \
                  https://192.168.1.2/api/carp/promote || true
              else
                echo "OPNsense VM healthy"
              fi
          restartPolicy: OnFailure
EOF

kubectl apply -f opnsense-monitor.yaml
                </code></pre>
            </div>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">API Key Configuration</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">On Dell 210 OPNsense:</p>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>System → Access → Users → Add API user</li>
                <li>Generate API key and secret</li>
                <li>Grant CARP management privileges</li>
                <li>Update monitor script with actual credentials</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Troubleshooting</h2>
            
            <div class="warning" style="background-color: var(--light-color); border-left: 4px solid var(--warning-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <h3 style="color: var(--warning-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Problem: CARP Not Syncing</h3>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Symptoms:</strong> Both nodes show MASTER or BACKUP, no automatic failover</p>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Solution:</strong></p>
                <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                    <li>Verify VHID Group IDs match on both systems</li>
                    <li>Check CARP passwords are identical</li>
                    <li>Ensure firewall rules allow CARP multicast (224.0.0.18)</li>
                    <li>Verify network connectivity between nodes</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); border-left: 4px solid var(--info-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <h3 style="color: var(--info-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Problem: Kubernetes Pods Not Starting</h3>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Symptoms:</strong> Pods stuck in Pending or ContainerCreating state</p>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Solution:</strong></p>
                <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                    <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code>
# Check node status
kubectl get nodes -o wide

# Check pod logs
kubectl describe pod <pod-name>

# Verify CNI plugin
kubectl get pods -n kube-system | grep flannel

# Check kubelet logs
journalctl -u kubelet -f
                    </code></pre>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); border-left: 4px solid var(--warning-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <h3 style="color: var(--warning-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Problem: VM Network Performance Issues</h3>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Symptoms:</strong> High latency, packet drops, low throughput</p>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Solution:</strong></p>
                <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                    <li>Enable multiqueue for VirtIO network adapters</li>
                    <li>Consider PCI passthrough for dedicated NICs</li>
                    <li>Verify CPU affinity settings</li>
                    <li>Check for CPU steal time in VMs</li>
                    <li>Monitor host network utilization</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Maintenance and Operations</h2>
            
            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Backup Procedures</h3>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>Proxmox:</strong> Use vzdump for VM backups</li>
                <li><strong>OPNsense:</strong> Automated XML configuration backups via cron</li>
                <li><strong>Kubernetes:</strong> Consider Velero for cluster backup</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Monitoring and Scaling</h3>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>Prometheus:</strong> Deploy in K8s for metrics collection</li>
                <li><strong>Grafana:</strong> Visualize CARP states and system health</li>
                <li><strong>Worker Nodes:</strong> Add K8s worker VMs for horizontal scaling</li>
                <li><strong>MetalLB:</strong> Implement for K8s load balancing behind OPNsense</li>
            </ul>

            <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code>
# Monitor CARP status
watch -n 5 'ifconfig | grep carp'

# Check Kubernetes cluster health
kubectl get nodes,pods --all-namespaces

# Proxmox system status
pvesh get /nodes/pve-r710/status
                </code></pre>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <div class="success" style="background-color: var(--light-color); border-left: 4px solid var(--success-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0;">
